<glossary>
<definition id="fs-id1500320"><term>cardiac muscle</term> <meaning id="fs-id1075664">heart muscle, under involuntary control, composed of striated cells that attach to form fibers, each cell contains a single nucleus, contracts autonomously</meaning></definition>
<definition id="fs-id1502075"><term>myocyte</term> <meaning id="fs-id1516236">muscle cells</meaning></definition>
<definition id="fs-id1435347"><term>skeletal muscle</term> <meaning id="fs-id1501456">usually attached to bone, under voluntary control, each cell is a fiber that is multinucleated and striated</meaning></definition>
<definition id="fs-id1432081"><term>smooth muscle</term> <meaning id="fs-id1475477">under involuntary control, moves internal organs, cells contain a single nucleus, are spindle-shaped, and do not appear striated; each cell is a fiber</meaning></definition>
<definition id="fs-id1481696"><term>striation</term> <meaning id="fs-id1501025">alignment of parallel actin and myosin filaments which form a banded pattern</meaning></definition>
</glossary>
